# Cursor rules for packages/annotate

## Project context
You are building `packages/annotate/` inside the CodeGuru monorepo.
Read CONTEXT.md in this directory for the full architecture and build plan.

## Code style
- TypeScript strict mode
- All styles inline via style={{}} — no CSS files, no CSS modules, no Tailwind
- React functional components with hooks only — no class components
- Named exports for all components, default export for the main wrapper
- Core engine (core/) must have ZERO React imports — pure TypeScript only
- Small, focused files — one component per file, one concern per module

## When generating code
- Follow the architecture in CONTEXT.md exactly
- Match the visual prototype (takeoff-annotate-v3.jsx) for all styling
- Use the exact colors, font sizes, and animations from the prototype
- All state changes must trigger URL hash updates via writeSessionToURL()
- Every click handler must check the current mode before acting
- Pin positions are absolute (x, y in pixels from surface top-left)
- Session encoding uses the minified key map from CONTEXT.md

## Component patterns
- Use React.createContext for shared state (mode, session, userName)
- useCallback for all event handlers passed as props
- useRef for the surface element (for coordinate calculation)
- useState with initializer functions for localStorage reads

## Don't
- Don't add any external dependencies beyond React and React DOM
- Don't use CSS-in-JS libraries (styled-components, emotion, etc.)
- Don't use localStorage for session state — URL hash is the source of truth
- Don't use localStorage for anything except the user's name
- Don't build Takeoff cloud features — URL state only for v1
- Don't add light theme — dark only for v1
- Don't use position: fixed for anything except the FloatingPill
- Don't add tests yet — manual testing only for v1
- Don't modify anything outside packages/annotate/
